{"title":"Bigfoot Spotted, Ritchey’s First Ever Flat Pedal","link":"https://bikerumor.com/bigfoot-spotted-ritcheys-first-ever-flat-pedal/","date":1747385880000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-hero.webp\" width=\"1280\" height=\"721\" alt=\"(Photos / Ritchey Design)\" /></p>\n<p>Northern California’s <a href=\"https://ritcheylogic.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Ritchey Design</a> has entered the flat pedal game with the launch of its first flat pedal, the <a href=\"https://ritcheylogic.com/bike/pedals/comp-bigfoot-pedals\" target=\"_blank\">Ritchey</a> <a href=\"https://ritcheylogic.com/bike/pedals/comp-bigfoot-pedals\" target=\"_blank\">Comp Bigfoot</a>. Injection-molded from reinforced nylon, the new pedals are both light and strong. And we’re kinda surprised it took more than 50 years for Ritchey to make a platform pedal. Strange, right?</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Ritchey Comp Bigfoot light composite platform pedals</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-first-pic.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"721\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-first-pic.webp\" alt=\"Ritchey Comp Bigfoot Flat Pedal first pic\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-first-pic.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-first-pic-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-first-pic-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-first-pic-768x433.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-first-pic-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a><figcaption><em>(Photos / Ritchey Design)</em></figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>At just $45 / 45€, the new Ritchey Comp Bigfoot is affordable as well. The 105 x 108.5mm slightly concave platform will give the rider control, confidence, and pedaling efficiency. And at 18.5mm thick, they balance a decently low height while ensuring strength and stability.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-profile.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"721\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-profile.webp\" alt=\"Ritchey Comp Bigfoot Flat Pedal profile\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-profile.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-profile-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-profile-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-profile-768x433.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-profile-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Comp Bigfoot is loaded with nine replaceable and adjustable anti-slip traction pins per side. This should almost guarantee solid shoe grip, whether on your city commuter, backcountry adventure ride, or trail mountain bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-corner.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"721\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-corner.webp\" alt=\"Ritchey Comp Bigfoot Flat Pedal corner\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-corner.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-corner-297x167.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-corner-120x68.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-corner-768x433.webp 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-corner-1200x675.webp 1200w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>These bad boys weigh in at a modest 360 grams per pair, and should have no problem holding as well as many heavier aluminum counterparts.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-mojave.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"984\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-mojave.webp\" alt=\"Ritchey Comp Bigfoot Flat Pedal mojave\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-mojave.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-mojave-297x228.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-mojave-120x92.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-mojave-768x590.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>Mojave Sand</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-black.webp\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"989\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-black.webp\" alt=\"Ritchey Comp Bigfoot Flat Pedal black\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-black.webp 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-black-297x229.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-black-120x93.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-black-768x593.webp 768w\" /></a><figcaption>BA Black</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Ritchey Comp Bigfoot  – Dimension &amp; Tech Specs</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-tech-drawing-e1747342432350.webp\"><img width=\"1003\" height=\"625\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-tech-drawing-e1747342432350.webp\" alt=\"Ritchey Comp Bigfoot Flat Pedal tech drawing\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-tech-drawing-e1747342432350.webp 1003w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-tech-drawing-e1747342432350-297x185.webp 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-tech-drawing-e1747342432350-120x75.webp 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/Ritchey-Comp-Bigfoot-Flat-Pedal-tech-drawing-e1747342432350-768x479.webp 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>fiber-reinforced nylon body</li>\n\n\n\n<li>chromoly axles</li>\n\n\n\n<li>sealed cartridge outer bearing</li>\n\n\n\n<li>glide bushing inner bearing</li>\n\n\n\n<li>63mm pedal Q-factor (crank-to-pedal center distance)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>9.25mm pedal stack height</li>\n\n\n\n<li>9 replaceable, adjustable anti-slip pins per side</li>\n\n\n\n<li>weight: 360g per pair, claimed</li>\n\n\n\n<li>colors: BA Black available now, Mojave Sand coming later this summer</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Pick a pair up now for $45 / 45€ directly from <a href=\"https://ritcheylogic.com/bike/pedals/comp-bigfoot-pedals\" target=\"_blank\">Ritchey’s webshop</a>, or from Ritchey’s global network of independent bike shops &amp; retailers.</p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://ritcheylogic.com/\" target=\"_blank\">RitchyLogic.com</a></em></p>\n\n\n\n<p></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bigfoot-spotted-ritcheys-first-ever-flat-pedal/\">Bigfoot Spotted, Ritchey’s First Ever Flat Pedal</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"a571bf88716e06232cda3318bee87fa7aff53e19aa0a249e6059d523fe61d2e0","category":"Cycling"}